Full Description: Carmack Moving and Storage is Fairfax County, Virginia’s premiere moving and storage provider, bringing over 28 year’s experience to area residents. With a fully trained staff and state of the art equipment, the team of professionals at Carmack Moving and Storage is ready to tackle any sized move whether in town or around the globe.   Carmack Moving and Storage | Moving Services Carmack Moving and Storage offers top quality relocation services for residential and commercial clients. The group utilizes a vast network of equipment and the industry’s most courteous labor professionals for each and every job.  Every expert mover at Carmack Moving and Storage has been expressly trained to work efficiently and effectively to ensure a smooth transition. And, Carmack Moving and Storage takes special care with heirlooms and other treasured items. The group is especially skilled and equipped to handle antique vehicles and musical equipment. Storage Options Carmack Moving and Storage goes to great lengths to ensure that each crate, box, or free-standing object is marked and inventoried, ensuring their accessibility. With these steps in place, Carmack Moving and Storage can promise a stress-free storage experience. They have a clean, temperature controlled storage facility, with competitive rates and above average customer service.  Carmack Moving and Storage only uses the best materials when palletizing their clients’ precious personal items. With Carmack Moving and Storage’s dedicated record keeping department, constantly monitored grounds, and neatly palletized facility, customers are guaranteed the best storage experience they will ever have.  Staging Services Realtors and home sellers can take advantage of home staging services presented by Carmack Moving and Storage. Staging services include a free crate and one month of free storage for your crate while your home is on the market.  Carmack Moving and Storage | Additional Services Carmack Moving and Storage offers expert packing and unpacking services. They can transport furniture, antiques, and other valuable items to their storage facility or directly to the client’s destination. In addition to local moves, Carmack Moving and Storage also offers interstate hauling. Valuation is provided for each move, which covers damage or loss due to company negligence. Carmack Moving and Storage has a very low claims rate but does suggest purchasing additional valuation to protect against travel related mishaps. Carmack Moving and Storage can facilitate this transaction and will happily help determine an appropriate dollar amount of coverage needed based on the weight of your shipment. Carmack Moving and Storage provides a Bill of Lading for each project. This document serves as a receipt and clearly outlines Carmack Moving and Storage’s responsibilities and serves to protect the client – many service providers simply quote the job and end their paper trail.  The terms and conditions of your contract will be provided for your review prior to your move date. Additional products and services may be available through prior arrangement with Carmack Moving and Storage. Costs Jobs are priced either hourly or per project, based on cargo weight. Carmack Moving and Storage provides free estimates. About Carmack Moving and Storage Carmack Moving and Storage has been growing since Rob Carmack got behind the wheel of his first moving truck in 1985. Since then, Carmack Moving and Storage has been proving residents of Northern Virginia, and the entire metro area, the most reliable and professional relocation services available. Rob takes the time to personally connect with each staff member, ensuring they understand his values of reliability and responsibility.  Carmack Moving and Storage is a family-oriented company and strives for 100% satisfaction. To contact Carmack Moving and Storage for a free, no obligation quote, call them at 703.378.1616 or toll-free at 866.627.4420. You may also email their administrative staff at info@carmackmoving.com. For home staging services, call Julia Silva at 703.378.1616.

Description: Attorney Ryan B. Addison and his dedicated staff are here to help you in your time of need.
Full Description: Attorney Ryan B. Addison lives in Mocksville, North Carolina, with his wife and two young children. Ryan loves NC State athletics, professional football, and spending time with his family and friends. He also gives his resources to local organizations of importance to his family and community at large. Born in Louisiana to a military family, Ryan has lived all over the country; however, he has spent the majority of the last thirty-plus years in North Carolina. After completing high school in nearby Greensboro, he graduated from North Carolina State University with a degree in history. From there, he attended law school in suburban Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. After law school, Ryan worked as a judicial law clerk in the trial and appellate courts of Pennsylvania for a number of years. He left the court system there to work for a law firm before eventually finding his way home. Ryan has been licensed to practice law in North Carolina since 2002. Prior to opening the Law Offices of Ryan B. Addison in 2008, Ryan worked as a magistrate, a legal instructor, and a contract attorney for a large local firm. He is a member of the North Carolina State Bar, North Carolina Bar Association, North Carolina Advocates for Justice, 19C District (Rowan County) Bar, and 22B (Davie County/Davidson County) Bar. He is also certified as a District Court Arbitrator as well as a Superior Court Mediator.

Full Description: The National Pancreas Foundation provides hope for those suffering from pancreatitis and pancreatic cancer through funding research, advocacy, & education. The National Pancreas Foundation (NPF) raises and manages a charitable foundation from which grants are made directly to researchers seeking to resolve the challenging medical problems of pancreatic diseases. A support network is being developed for individuals suffering the isolating and debilitating conditions associated with pancreatic disease. The NPF and its founding members and volunteers are committed to maximum efficiency. The Foundation’s goal is to direct as much of their revenue to programs. To achieve this they rely heavily on the invaluable donations of time, energy and financial support of the many friends and interested parties who have been touched by the suffering of so many people. Research grant proposals from a wide variety of researchers are solicited. With the help of the Foundation’s Grant Review Council, the NPF makes grants to those whose proposals appear most likely to lead to scientific advancements in the field of pancreatic disease.

Description: BioMed SA is a non-profit, membership-based organization, supported in part by the City of San Antonio.
Full Description: The Healthcare Bioscience Development Corporation, d/b/a BioMed SA, was formed by San Antonio community and industry leaders during 2005 to build upon the city's impressive base of biomedical assets and raise its visibility nationally and beyond. This initiative was based on the realization that, despite the significant size of the local healthcare and bioscience industry and its importance to the local economy, San Antonio is not well recognized for its unique biomedical assets. The City of San Antonio, Bexar County and CPS Energy provided grants totaling $250,000 to launch BioMed SA as a non-profit corporation and public/private partnership. This was done at the request of Henry Cisneros and Joe Krier, representing The Greater San Antonio Chamber of Commerce. BioMed SA subsequently received tax-exempt status from the IRS as a 501(c)(6) organization. Following a nationwide search and selection process, Ann Stevens was hired from San Antonio's bioscience community as President, effective November 1, 2005. She and Director of Membership and Administrative Services, Donna Miller, constitute the initial staff. BioMed SA is a non-profit, membership-based organization, supported in part by the City of San Antonio.
